# E2E Testing Standard

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/testing/e2e.md](../../docs/agent/standards/testing/e2e.md)

- E2E tests use Supertest against the real NestJS application (bootstrapped via `Test.createTestingModule`).
- Every endpoint in `docs/api/openapi.yaml` must have at least one E2E test.
- Cover: correct status code, correct response shape, correct error codes (per OpenAPI spec).
- Auth: create real JWT tokens via `POST /api/v1/auth/login` at the start of each test suite.
- RBAC: test that the wrong role returns 403 for all role-protected endpoints.
- Seed data: use factories; truncate tables in `afterAll`.
- File naming: `{domain}.e2e-spec.ts` in `test/e2e/`.
